org.smartfrog.sfcore.utils
Class Spinner

java.lang.Object
  org.smartfrog.sfcore.utils.Spinner

public class Spinner
extends java.lang.Object

Utility class to spin and timeout. It can sleep for a predefined wait interval, and will, if interrupted, throw a TimedOutIOException in such a situation.

After timeout, any exception set with setLastThrown(Throwable) will be included as a nested exception, for more meaningful stack traces

Spinner

public Spinner(java.lang.String operation,
               long waitInterval,
               long timeout)
Spin until timeout. The timeout is constructed from now+timeout, so create this object immediately before you need it

Parameters:
operation - operation to be used in error messages
waitInterval - interval in milliseconds for a sleep
timeout - timeout in milliseconds.
Method Detail

sleep

public void sleep()
           throws java.io.IOException
Sleep for a defined period of time. Before sleeping, a check is made for the operation having timed out already.

Throws:
java.io.InterruptedIOException - if the operation was interrupted
java.io.IOException - if the last thrown exception was of type IOException
TimedOutIOException - if we have already timed out and the last thrown exception is of a different type
